  <h2>What remediation measures should you apply after the attack?</h2>

  <p>With the analysis complete, we implement the following measures:</p>

  <h3>How do you install Fail2ban for automatic blocking?</h3>

  <p>Automatically blocks IPs after X failed attempts:</p>

  <pre style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;">apt install fail2ban
systemctl enable fail2ban</code></pre>

  <p>Configuration in <code>/etc/fail2ban/jail.local</code>:</p>

  <pre style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;">[sshd]
enabled = true
port = ssh
filter = sshd
logpath = /var/log/auth.log
maxretry = 5
bantime = 3600
findtime = 600</code></pre>

  <p><strong>Result:</strong> After 5 failed attempts in 10 minutes, the IP is blocked for 1 hour.</p>

  <h3>How do you set up public key authentication for SSH?</h3>

  <p>Disable SSH passwords and use public keys only:</p>

  <pre style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;"># Generate a key on the client
ssh-keygen -t ed25519

# Copy the key to the server
ssh-copy-id usuario@servidor</code></pre>

  <p>Edit <code>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</code>:</p>

  <pre style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;">PasswordAuthentication no
PubkeyAuthentication yes</code></pre>

  <p>Restart SSH:</p>

  <pre style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;">systemctl restart sshd</code></pre>

  <p><strong>Result:</strong> Brute-force attacks are completely neutralized.</p>

